<Text: The Saint Gevork of Mughni Church (Armenian: Մուղնեցվոց Սուրբ Գևորգ Եկեղեցի Georgian: წმინდა გიორგის მუღნის ეკლესია ) also known as Saint George of Mughni Church ("Gevork" in Armenian is cognate with "George") is a 13th-century Armenian church in Tbilisi, Georgia that was entirely rebuilt in 1756.>
